### Weight and Jump Height

A heavy character can't jump as high as a light one, given the same leg strength.

```scheme
(motion
  (beat 85)
  (let ((t (frame)))
    (entity rabbit
      (pos 150 (- 280 (max 0 (- (* 6 t) (* 0.15 t t)))))
      (radius 8)
      (color 220 200 180))
    (entity elephant
      (pos 350 (- 280 (max 0 (- (* 3 t) (* 0.25 t t)))))
      (radius 22)
      (color 120 120 110))
    (until (> t 80))))
```

[VISUAL: Parabolic jumps — rabbit arcs high, elephant barely leaves the ground.]

Same gravity-like quadratic term, different initial velocity and weight factor. The elephant's shallow arc communicates mass.

```scheme
(motion
  (beat 70)
  (let ((t (frame))
        (launch-frame 20))
    (entity flea
      (pos 200 (if (< t launch-frame)
                   280
                   (- 280 (* 8 (- t launch-frame)) (* -0.2 (expt (- t launch-frame) 2)))))
      (radius 3)
      (color 100 100 100))
    (until (> t 120))))
```

[VISUAL: Flea leaping — explosive takeoff, high arc, then gravity pulls it down.]

Tiny mass allows extreme jump height relative to body size.

