### Carrying and Effort

A character carrying a heavy load moves differently: slower, lower, more deliberate.

```scheme
(motion
  (beat 60)
  (let ((t (frame)))
    (entity unladen
      (pos (+ 100 (* 3.5 t)) 200)
      (radius 8)
      (color 200 200 255))
    (entity laden
      (pos (+ 100 (* 1.8 t)) 260)
      (radius 10)
      (color 200 200 255))
    (until (> t 120))))
```

[VISUAL: Two circles moving rightward — unladen travels faster, laden slower and perhaps lower (implied hunched posture).]

Same time, different speeds. The laden entity's reduced velocity reads as effort under load.

```scheme
(motion
  (beat 70)
  (let ((t (frame)))
    (entity worker-empty
      (pos (+ 150 (* 2.5 t)) (+ 220 (* 3 (sin (* 0.25 t)))))
      (radius 7)
      (color 180 180 200))
    (entity worker-crate
      (pos (+ 150 (* 1.5 t)) (+ 250 (* 1 (sin (* 0.15 t)))))
      (radius 9)
      (color 180 180 200))
    (until (> t 140))))
```

[VISUAL: Walking gaits — empty worker bounces jauntily, loaded worker's step is low and plodding.]

Vertical oscillation (gait bounce) reduced when carrying weight. Frequency and amplitude both drop.

