### Weight Distribution and Tipping

An object with uneven weight distribution tips when pushed; a balanced one slides.

```scheme
(motion
  (beat 80)
  (let ((t (frame)))
    (entity top-heavy-tower
      (pos (+ 200 (* 0.5 t)) 200)
      (rotation (* 0.3 t))
      (radius 12)
      (color 140 100 80))
    (entity balanced-cube
      (pos (+ 320 (* 0.5 t)) 200)
      (rotation 0)
      (radius 12)
      (color 100 100 140))
    (until (> t 100))))
```

[VISUAL: Both pushed rightward at same rate — tower rotates (tipping), cube slides without rotating.]

Rotation reveals center-of-mass offset. The tower's spin communicates instability.

```scheme
(motion
  (beat 75)
  (let ((t (frame)))
    (entity vase
      (pos 200 (+ 200 (* 0.1 t)))
      (rotation (* 0.2 t))
      (radius 10)
      (color 200 180 160))
    (until (> t 120))))
```

[VISUAL: Vase tipping forward as it slides down — combined translation and rotation.]

The coupled motion (slide + tip) shows weight pulling it off balance.

