### Swing and Follow-Through

A heavy object swung by a handle carries the wielder forward; a light one stops on command.

```scheme
(motion
  (beat 80)
  (let ((t (frame)))
    (entity wand
      (pos (+ 200 (* 60 (sin (* 0.15 t)))) 200)
      (radius 5)
      (color 200 150 100))
    (entity sledgehammer
      (pos (+ 350 (* 50 (sin (* 0.08 t)))) 200)
      (radius 14)
      (color 80 80 80))
    (until (> t 140))))
```

[VISUAL: Horizontal oscillation (swing back and forth) — wand flicks crisply, sledgehammer swings with slow, heavy momentum.]

Frequency difference: the sledgehammer's mass resists direction change, lengthening the swing period.

```scheme
(motion
  (beat 70)
  (let ((t (frame)))
    (entity flag
      (pos 200 (+ 200 (* 30 (sin (* 0.2 t)))))
      (radius 6)
      (color 255 100 100))
    (entity wrecking-ball
      (pos 350 (+ 200 (* 50 (sin (* 0.06 t)))))
      (radius 20)
      (color 70 70 70))
    (until (> t 180))))
```

[VISUAL: Vertical pendulum swings — flag flutters, wrecking ball swings ponderously.]

Amplitude and period both encode weight. The ball's wide, slow arc communicates mass.

