### Weight in Free Fall Formation

Skydivers of different weights fall at different rates (in reality, drag matters more than mass, but animators often show heavy = faster).

```scheme
(motion
  (beat 90)
  (let ((t (frame)))
    (entity jumper-light
      (pos 180 (+ 80 (* 1.8 t)))
      (radius 7)
      (color 200 200 255))
    (entity jumper-heavy
      (pos 250 (+ 80 (* 2.8 t)))
      (radius 10)
      (color 100 100 140))
    (until (> t 150))))
```

[VISUAL: Two falling figures — heavier one descends faster (animator's shorthand for \"dense\").]

Constant velocities differing by weight. Real physics involves drag, but the cue is clear.

