### Effort in Acceleration

Pushing a heavy object to speed requires visible, sustained effort.

```scheme
(motion
  (beat 70)
  (let ((t (frame)))
    (entity cart-empty
      (pos (+ 150 (* 0.04 t t)) 200)
      (radius 10)
      (color 180 180 200))
    (entity cart-loaded
      (pos (+ 150 (* 0.008 t t)) 250)
      (radius 14)
      (color 120 100 80))
    (until (> t 130))))
```

[VISUAL: Both accelerating from rest — empty cart picks up speed, loaded cart barely moves.]

Quadratic position growth at different rates. The loaded cart's shallow curve shows the struggle.

