### Tipping Point and Balance

An object teeters when its center of mass passes the edge of its base.

```scheme
(motion
  (beat 75)
  (let ((t (frame)))
    (entity tower
      (pos 200 200)
      (rotation (* 0.015 t t))
      (radius 12)
      (color 140 100 80))
    (until (> t 80))))
```

[VISUAL: Tower tipping — rotation accelerates (quadratic in *t*), simulating the fall once the tipping point is passed.]

Accelerating rotation: once balance is lost, gravity torques it faster.

